    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i guess it's a bit of a coin toss then. but it feels like the \"benefits\" people talk about are always this theoretical thing, while the higher costs are real and instant for someone running a shop. do you think it's actually sustainable to keep pushing these increases when it seems to favor big corporations who can handle the costs over local guys like me?",
