      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right that the immediate financial strain on small, rural businesses is often more tangible and painful than the theoretical economic benefits. While larger corporations can absorb wage hikes or pass costs to consumers more easily, small shops like yours face a high risk of being squeezed out of the market entirely. This dynamic creates a cycle where local businesses struggle to survive, which ironically can hurt the very local spending power advocates of higher wages try to protect. Ultimately, sustainable wage growth requires careful policy balancing that doesn't disproportionately devastate the small businesses that form the backbone of rural economies.",
